cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on protocol stacks for IoT and their performance in different scenarios. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper may discuss security concerns related to the different protocols. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the scalability of the different protocols in multi-hop scenarios. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the control and management of IoT devices using the different protocols. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may discuss the information transmission and processing aspects of the different protocols.
